## Answer

**Core bug**: `currentStep` advances past `steps.length` on `message_end`, making all subsequent `tool_execution_start/end` handlers no-ops. Feed state rendered once and never re-rendered with actual tool progress. Substeps preserved in data but not reflected because step pointer is out of bounds.

